Algorithm: Bank System Using Linked List (Menu Driven)
1. Start
2. Define Structure
Create a structure Node with:
id
name
balance
pointer next
3. Initialize
Set head = NULL
4. Repeat Until User Chooses Exit
Display Menu:
Create Account
Display Accounts
Deposit Money
Withdraw Money
Delete Account
Exit
Input choice
5. Perform Operation Based on Choice
Case 1: Create Account
Create a new node
Input:
ID
Name
Initial Balance
Set newNode->next = NULL
If head == NULL
Set head = newNode
Else
Traverse to last node
Attach new node at end
Display success message
Case 2: Display Accounts
If head == NULL
Print "No accounts available"
Else
Traverse from head
For each node:
Display ID, Name, Balance
Case 3: Deposit Money
Input account ID
Call search function:
Traverse list to find matching ID
If account found:
Input deposit amount
Add amount to balance
Print success message
Else:
Print "Account not found"
Case 4: Withdraw Money
Input account ID
Search account
If found:
Input withdrawal amount
If balance ≥ amount:
Subtract amount
Print success
Else:
Print "Insufficient Balance"
Else:
Print "Account not found"
Case 5: Delete Account
Input account ID
Set:
temp = head
prev = NULL
If first node matches ID:
Move head to next node
Delete old node
Else:
Traverse list to find node
Keep track of previous node
If not found:
Print "Account not found"
Else:
Link prev->next = temp->next
Delete node
Print success message
Case 6: Exit
Terminate program
Default Case
Print "Invalid choice"
6. End Loop When Choice = 6
7. Stop
